The paper deals with the segmentation of 3D point clouds, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. The use of a 3D convolutional neural network suggests that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The focus on architectural models and the use of primitive-based segmentation techniques suggest that the paper may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The use of a hierarchical tree for segmentation suggests that the paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of an energy function and the classification of segments suggest that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of a convolutional neural network for classification suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
